{
  "texts": [
    "… Pix2Pix uses a conditional generative adversarial network (cGAN) to learn a mapping from an input image to an output image.",
    "… to learn image mappings which lets our models learn topological features and space organization directly from floor plan images.",
    "We control the type of information that the model learns by formatting images.",
    "As an example, just showing our model the shape of a parcel and its associated building footprint yields a model able to create typical building footprints given a parcel's shape, Chaillou (2023) describes the supervised-learning strategy that reduces the essentially comprehensive architectural task to image processing.",
    "Leaving aside hundreds of thousands of images, each of them labeled by humans, that are a precondition for the \"statistics\" to work properly, the strategy has proven a no-go in terms both of the competent AECO workflows and computing power."
  ]
}